Male palp:
distal 1/2 section of dorsal palpal cymbium with scopula (
Fig. 9c
). Conductor (C) with dense tubercles (almost 2/3 section of C is covered with tubercles), and with discoid platform-shaped extension prolaterally (as indicated by arrow in 
Fig. 9a
). Embolus slender; embolic base broad, without apophyses (
Figs 9a– c
, 
10a–c
). Palpal tibia with a cluster of long hairs at retrolateral side (
Fig. 9a
). Palpal femur with a cambered bulge (
Fig. 9d
).
